The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, January 29, 2004 				 Bombay Dyeing spins higher net
 OUR BUREAU																								Mumbai, Jan. 28: Bombay Dyeing amp; Manufacturing Co Ltd more than doubled its net profit at Rs 13.13 crore for the third quarter ended December 31, 2003, compared with Rs 5.94 crore in the corresponding previous quarter. 																								Total income (net of excise) during the period under review has decreased to Rs 248.37 crore from Rs 251.08 crore recorded in the same period last year, the company informed the stock exchange here today.  IPCL net up a shade																								IPCL has posted an 8 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 81 crore for the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 as against Rs 75 crore in the same period last fiscal. 																								Turnover increased by 79.4 per cent to Rs 2,778 crore as against Rs 1,548 crore in the year-ago period, the company said.																								Net profit and turnover for the nine-month period ended December 31 stood at Rs 174 crore (Rs 114 crore) and Rs 5,478 crore (Rs 3,656 crore) respectively. Sterlite net up 43%																								Sterlite Industries (India) Ltd has reported a 43.19 per cent jump in net profit for the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 at Rs 50.79 crore compared with Rs 35.47 crore in the same period last fiscal. Net sales showed a 49.15 per cent growth at Rs 821.19 crore (Rs 550.57 crore). 																								For the nine-month period ended December, the company reported a higher net profit at Rs 123.48 crore (Rs 107.1 crore) and net sales of Rs 2,185.44 crore (Rs 1,546.5 crore). NPIL net at Rs 37cr																								Nicholas Piramal India Ltd (NPIL) has posted a higher net profit at Rs 37.5 crore in the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 as against Rs 21.1 crore in the same period last fiscal. Net sales grew to Rs 262.02 crore (Rs 219.5 crore), the company said.																								Net profit and sales for the nine months ended December 31 stood at Rs 110.4 crore (Rs 78.49 crore) and Rs 836.77 crore (Rs 697.03 crore) respectively, it said. 																								The above results of 2003-04 are not comparable with those of the corresponding previous periods as a result of Global Drug and Fine Chemicals Ltds merger with NPIL from January 1, 2003. Raymond net jumps																								Raymond Ltd has reported a 60 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 30.55 crore for the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 as against Rs 19.10 crore year-on-year. Net sales were up marginally at Rs 277.44 crore (Rs 275.38 crore).
